President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation ordering that the flag of the United States be flown at full-staff at the White House, as well as all public buildings and grounds, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government. This directive is effective from sunset on December 17, 2016. The proclamation also states that the flag should be flown at full-staff on the same day at all U.S. embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The proclamation is signed by President Obama on December 16, 2016.